00:09:25,720 --> 00:09:27,600
真是的 不是说要对我保密吗
I thought it was a secret.

182
00:09:27,680 --> 00:09:30,310
我对你哪有秘密啊
I don't keep anything from you.

183
00:09:30,400 --> 00:09:32,810
听起来不像是好事
It doesn't sound like anything good.

184
00:09:33,570 --> 00:09:35,070
我们要不要帮她
Should we help her?

185
00:09:35,570 --> 00:09:40,240
不用 那我就没必要 把她送到那里去了
No. Then I sent her there for no reason.

186
00:09:41,530 --> 00:09:43,330
她会解决的
She will do fine on her own.

187
00:09:43,410 --> 00:09:44,240
好
Okay.

188
00:09:45,490 --> 00:09:46,450
稍等一下
One moment.

189
00:09:48,330 --> 00:09:50,920
爸 我马上就到了
Dad, your son will be arriving soon.

190
00:09:51,630 --> 00:09:53,250
民赫要过来向你问好
Minhyeok is on his way to say hello.

191
00:09:53,840 --> 00:09:55,000
民赫回来了？
Minhyeok is back?

192
00:09:55,090 --> 00:09:57,090
对 他前天刚回国
Yes. He arrived the day before.

193
00:09:57,420 --> 00:10:00,260
他说想尽快来见你
He wanted to see you as soon as possible.

194
00:10:01,260 --> 00:10:02,720
你忙的话 我就让他回去
I can tell him to leave if you're busy.

195
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:04,470
不用让他回去
There's no need to do that.

196
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:07,390
我们好久没见了 我见见他
It will be nice to see his face after such a while.

197
00:10:15,270 --> 00:10:16,570
你干吗
Geez. What are you doing?

198
00:10:17,280 --> 00:10:20,490
还能干吗 我在培训实习生啊
What am I doing? I'm training a probationary employee.

199
00:10:20,570 --> 00:10:22,030
你赶紧看完还给我
Read it quickly and give it back.

200
00:10:23,530 --> 00:10:26,620
品性不好 性格也不好…
Bad character, bad personality...

201
00:10:26,790 --> 00:10:27,950
上面是这么说的
is what it says here.

202
00:10:28,040 --> 00:10:29,620
样样都不好
Bad, bad...

203
00:10:29,700 --> 00:10:31,120
这家伙简直是人渣啊
What a piece of trash.

204
00:10:31,210 --> 00:10:33,170
我撞得好
I did well by crashing his car, yes.

205
00:10:33,380 --> 00:10:35,170
我就说我看人很准吧
I am such a good judge of character.

206
00:10:36,170 --> 00:10:38,250
怎么样 你想出计划了吗
So, were you able to come up with a plan?

207
00:10:38,340 --> 00:10:39,380
没有
No.

208
00:10:42,130 --> 00:10:43,390
我还在想
I'm still thinking about it.

209
00:10:43,970 --> 00:10:45,050
还在想？
Thinking?

210
00:10:45,220 --> 00:10:47,640
你还在脑子里不停地想吗
You're still working it out in your head?

211
00:10:48,970 --> 00:10:51,560
等你想好了 就告诉我
Let me know when you're done thinking.

212
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:54,440
毕竟我在培训实习生嘛
I'm the lawyer training a probationary employee.

213
00:10:54,520 --> 00:10:55,520
好的
Yes.

214
00:10:57,360 --> 00:10:58,480
给你
Here you go.

215
00:11:06,320 --> 00:11:07,240
我能看见
I can see you.

216
00:11:07,830 --> 00:11:08,790
所以呢
So, what?

217
00:11:13,750 --> 00:11:14,790
你搞得我无话可说
I have no nothing to say.

218
00:11:22,260 --> 00:11:25,640
好 你在纽约过得愉快吗
So, did you enjoy your time in New York?

219
00:11:25,890 --> 00:11:29,220
是的 托你的福 我学到了很多
Yes. I learned so much, thanks to you.

220
00:11:30,640 --> 00:11:32,560
这怎么是托我的福
What is there to thank me?

221
00:11:32,640 --> 00:11:34,600
你是凭自己的本事去的
You went on your own merit.

222
00:11:34,810 --> 00:11:35,980
不是
Not at all.

223
00:11:36,310 --> 00:11:37,860
都是托你的福
It was all thanks to you, Mr. Baek.

224
00:11:38,190 --> 00:11:41,190
重要的是心意 不是吗
It's the heart that matters. The heart.

225
00:11:41,280 --> 00:11:43,360
多亏了你为他操心
Because of your moral support,

226
00:11:43,990 --> 00:11:47,030
我家民赫才能顺利地完成进修回国
Minhyeok was able to finish his training without a hitch.

227
00:11:47,530 --> 00:11:50,450
没错 全靠你为我费心 我才能学成归来
That's right. I was able to do well because of your care and attention.

228
00:11:50,540 --> 00:11:52,870
白代表 这都是托你的福
Thanks to you, Mr. Baek.

229
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:56,250
好 就当是托我的福吧
Fine, I will take the credit then.

230
00:11:57,330 --> 00:12:00,340
你看着他 心里一定很踏实吧
You must be so proud of Minhyeok.

231
00:12:00,420 --> 00:12:01,710
是啊
Yes, I am.

232
00:12:02,510 --> 00:12:04,170
我这么说不是因为他是我的儿子 但无论谁嫁给他
I don't say this because he's my son,

233
00:12:04,260 --> 00:12:05,340
我这么说不是因为他是我的儿子 但无论谁嫁给他
but whoever marries him will be a lucky girl.

234
00:12:05,430 --> 00:12:06,970
都是撞了大运
but whoever marries him will be a lucky girl.

235
00:12:09,050 --> 00:12:12,020
爸 我现在还不想结婚
Dad, I'm not ready to get married yet.

236
00:12:12,520 --> 00:12:14,890
我告诉过你 工作对我来说更重要
I told you work is more important to me.

237
00:12:15,770 --> 00:12:16,730
我…
I will...

238
00:12:18,150 --> 00:12:23,030
会在检察厅向着更高的地方前进
work for an even loftier purpose at the Prosecutor's Office.

239
00:12:24,820 --> 00:12:27,110
这就是这家伙的问题所在
This is what worries me about him.

240
00:12:27,200 --> 00:12:30,410
他得赶紧遇到一个好女孩 才能改变想法
I hope he meets a good woman so that he changes his mind.

241
00:12:30,910 --> 00:12:32,160
没关系
There's nothing wrong with it.

242
00:12:32,830 --> 00:12:34,950
他现在正是拼事业的时候
Now is the time to devote yourself to work.

243
00:12:35,290 --> 00:12:36,210
什么
What?

244
00:12:39,710 --> 00:12:42,750
不过一旦他有了喜欢的人 还是要让他马上结婚
Gosh. But I would marry him off as soon as he found anyone he liked.

245
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:44,630
我家玛丽…
My Mari...

246
00:12:45,720 --> 00:12:49,550
我也得让她快点结婚 真让人担心
should find someone soon. I'm worried.

247
00:12:49,640 --> 00:12:51,300
你不必为此担心
You don't need to worry about that!

248
00:12:51,930 --> 00:12:53,060
什么
What?

249
00:12:55,140 --> 00:12:58,520
玛丽会自己看着办的
Mari is very capable of taking care of herself.

250
00:13:01,020 --> 00:13:03,320
不过我怎么没看到她呢
Where is she anyway?

251
00:13:03,860 --> 00:13:07,740
玛丽是我的孙女 更应该凭实力进来
Mari is my granddaughter so she needs to come on her own merits.

252
00:13:08,110 --> 00:13:09,610
我让她去别的地方了
I sent her somewhere.

253
00:13:11,950 --> 00:13:13,030
哪里
Where?

254
00:13:18,670 --> 00:13:20,630
搜索 人权
SEARCH: HUMAN RIGHTS

255
00:13:22,340 --> 00:13:23,920
完成一行宾果
One bingo, one side.

256
00:13:30,430 --> 00:13:32,550
怎么了 你看什么
What is it? What are you looking at?

257
00:13:33,100 --> 00:13:34,180
我在工作
I'm working.

258
00:13:38,890 --> 00:13:40,140
完成两行宾果
Two bingo, one side.

259
00:13:58,160 --> 00:14:01,460
好 我们从案件概要开始吧
Good, let's start with the outline of the incident.

260
00:14:03,460 --> 00:14:06,300
枫津泰银公寓的保安金万福
The incident occurred when the security guard Kim Manbok

261
00:14:06,590 --> 00:14:09,880
刮伤了公寓业主千永裴的汽车 因此发生了这起案件
scratched the car of Cheon Yeongbae, a resident of Pungjin Taeeun Apartments.

262
00:14:09,970 --> 00:14:11,260
错 不对
Nope, that's not it.

263
00:14:11,840 --> 00:14:14,300
对于是否刮到 事实关系并不清楚
It's not clear whether it was scratched or not.

264
00:14:14,390 --> 00:14:15,970
你怎么能确定刮到了呢
So, how can you be sure?

265
00:14:16,060 --> 00:14:17,930
这正是我要说的
That's exactly what I'm saying.

266
00:14:18,140 --> 00:14:21,770
到底有没有刮到 还没等我们确认事实关系
Whether it was scratched or not couldn't be determined,

267
00:14:21,850 --> 00:14:24,270
千某就当着所有人的面
thanks to a certain Mr. Cheon so-and-so

268
00:14:24,610 --> 00:14:26,690
推着手推车撞上去了
who crashed a wagon into the car in front of everyone.

269
00:14:26,770 --> 00:14:29,690
对 就是这个
Yes! That's what I'm talking about.

270
00:14:29,780 --> 00:14:30,950
事实关系很明确
Those facts are crystal clear.

271
00:14:31,530 --> 00:14:33,280
实习的时候办这种案件比较好
This is a great case for a probationary employee.

272
00:14:33,780 --> 00:14:35,330
清晰的案件 很好
A clear-cut case, I like it.

273
00:14:36,410 --> 00:14:37,870
你是为了我才撞上去的吗
So, you crashed it for me?

274
00:14:37,950 --> 00:14:41,750
对 我是为了测试你是否有资格 来我们事务所实习
Sure. It is a test to see if you are qualified to join my practice.

275
00:14:41,830 --> 00:14:43,670
才故意撞上去的 你很感激我吧
I crashed it on purpose. Aren't you grateful?

276
00:14:43,750 --> 00:14:45,710
好 就当是这样吧
Let's say I am.

277
00:14:46,380 --> 00:14:47,630
第一种解决方案是
First proposal,

278
00:14:47,710 --> 00:14:51,260
支付五百万韩元 立即修好汽车
we pay five million won to get the car fixed right away.

279
00:14:52,430 --> 00:14:55,470
真是的 如果我要自掏腰包修车的话
Well, if I was going to pay out of pocket,

280
00:14:55,550 --> 00:14:58,430
还请你做我的律师干吗 对吧
I wouldn't have hired you as my lawyer. Don't you think so?

281
00:14:58,930 --> 00:15:00,600
而且打死我也没那么多钱
And I don't have that kind of money.

282
00:15:00,680 --> 00:15:02,890
-你一个律师连五百万韩元都没有吗 -我连五十万韩元也没有
-A lawyer doesn't have five million? -I don't even have 500,000.

283
00:15:02,980 --> 00:15:03,940
你还挺自豪啊
-Are you proud of that? -I am. I have righteousness and integrity.

284
00:15:04,020 --> 00:15:05,440
是挺自豪的 我很清正廉洁
-Are you proud of that? -I am. I have righteousness and integrity.

285
00:15:05,650 --> 00:15:07,820
-你太幼稚了 -我很幼稚吗
-That's so immature. -Is it?

286
00:15:07,900 --> 00:15:09,940
你干吗像小孩子一样幼稚
Why are you being so immature?

287
00:15:10,070 --> 00:15:12,740
玛丽正在绞尽脑汁找办法呢
Mari is trying to find a solution.

288
00:15:12,990 --> 00:15:15,030
你安静点 听她说吧
Be quiet, and let's listen to her.

289
00:15:15,620 --> 00:15:16,740
请继续吧
Please continue.

290
00:15:18,120 --> 00:15:19,580
第二种解决方案
Second proposal,

291
00:15:20,160 --> 00:15:21,830
如果不能用金钱达成和解的话
if it can't be resolved with money,

292
00:15:21,910 --> 00:15:24,370
那就要受到刑事处罚
he will be criminally prosecuted.

293
00:15:25,830 --> 00:15:28,710
如果没有钱 那就得拘留 当然我说的是千某
If Mr. Cheon so-and-so doesn't pay up, he should serve time.

294
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,960
我也想那样 但我不能被拘留
I wish I could, but I can't.

295
00:15:31,050 --> 00:15:33,550
这又是为什么 如果没有钱 那就用自由来交换
Why not? If you don't have money, you should pay with your time.

296
00:15:33,630 --> 00:15:35,680
如果我进去了 你在哪里实习呢
If I go to prison, where would you get your training?

297
00:15:36,390 --> 00:15:39,350
而且通常初犯不会被拘留
Besides, a first-time offender usually doesn't serve any time.

298
00:15:45,850 --> 00:15:46,900
第三种
Third,

299
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:50,820
衷心祈祷有另一个 更疯狂的人去撞他的车
We should give a heartfelt prayer for someone even crazier to hit his car.

300
00:15:53,030 --> 00:15:55,950
-长得真像 -眼睛长得很像
-That looks like her. -It's the eyes that look alike.

301
00:15:56,030 --> 00:15:57,410
真有意思
That was funny.

302
00:15:57,700 --> 00:15:59,620
干得不错
Nice try.

303
00:15:59,740 --> 00:16:00,990
我让你寻找解决办法
I told you to find solutions,

304
00:16:01,080 --> 00:16:03,410
但我看到的只有对指导律师的敌意
but all I see is animosity towards the mentoring lawyer.

305
00:16:04,250 --> 00:16:07,460
玛丽 我很失望 你还有别的吗
Mari, this is disappointing. Don't you have anything else?

306
00:16:08,580 --> 00:16:09,790
那么
Well then,

307
00:16:10,380 --> 00:16:12,210
我还有最后一个解决方案
I do have the last suggestion.

308
00:16:12,300 --> 00:16:14,880
我可以期待一下最后的解决方案吗
Can I expect your last suggestion to be any better?

309
00:16:14,970 --> 00:16:16,380
前面的那些可不怎么样
Your earlier ones were not good.

310
00:16:16,970 --> 00:16:17,930
当然
Of course.

311
00:16:19,390 --> 00:16:21,390
你会很喜欢的
I think you'll like it very much.

312
00:16:21,560 --> 00:16:24,520
是什么呢 是什么会让我很喜欢呢
What is it? What could be so good?

313
00:16:26,980 --> 00:16:28,440
她走过来干吗
Why is she coming closer?

314
00:16:28,520 --> 00:16:31,980
她把脸靠得这么近干吗
Why is she putting her face so close to mine?

315
00:16:34,820 --> 00:16:37,490
你不知道社交距离限制还没有解除吗
Don't you know we still need to socially distance ourselves?

316
00:16:41,330 --> 00:16:42,990
我把一千韩元还给你
I will give you your 1,000 won back.

317
00:16:46,620 --> 00:16:48,000
真痛快
Damn. That felt good.

318
00:16:50,790 --> 00:16:52,500
你要还给我吗 那实习呢
Giving it back? What about your training?

319
00:16:52,710 --> 00:16:55,340
反正律师事务所这么多 实习嘛 我会看着办的
There are other law offices. I'll take care of myself.

320
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:57,430
你还是担心你自己吧
You should worry about yourself.

321
00:16:57,510 --> 00:16:59,140
千永裴可不好对付
I don't think Cheon Yeongbae will go easy.

322
00:17:01,260 --> 00:17:04,520
事务长 我们改天一起喝杯烧酒吧
Mr. Sa, let's get together for soju some time.

323
00:17:04,600 --> 00:17:06,230
不要带自大的千某
Without the righteous Mr. Cheon so-and-so.

324
00:17:06,640 --> 00:17:09,350
他应该要忙着处理这个案子
Mr. Cheon so-and-so will be busy working on this case.

325
00:17:09,520 --> 00:17:11,440
-那么再见 -嗯 慢走
-Farewell. -Goodbye.

326
00:17:11,520 --> 00:17:13,070
等一下 这可不行
Wait, that's not right.

327
00:17:13,230 --> 00:17:15,070
你真是的 千律师 玛丽
Come on, Mr. Cheon. Mari!

328
00:17:15,150 --> 00:17:16,650
你不想在这里实习了吗
Don't you want to be a probationary employee?

329
00:17:17,150 --> 00:17:18,070
喂
Hey--

330
00:17:24,290 --> 00:17:26,040
玛丽 喝点乳酸菌饮料
Have a yogurt drink, Mari.

331
00:17:29,460 --> 00:17:30,750
干杯
Cheers.

332
00:17:30,880 --> 00:17:32,880
家营超市
HOMERUN MART

333
00:17:34,630 --> 00:17:38,550
玛丽 正如你所说 这种情况任谁看都会觉得荒唐
As you said, this doesn't make sense to anyone.

334
00:17:38,630 --> 00:17:41,390
不管怎么想 我都觉得这件事我解决不了
I don't think it was something I could resolve.

335
00:17:42,050 --> 00:17:45,560
而最重要的是 我感觉这里不适合我
Moreover, I don't think it's the right place for me.

336
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:49,520
当然还有很多更大更好的律师事务所
Of course, there are many law offices that are bigger and better.

337
00:17:49,980 --> 00:17:52,900
但其他事务所 会像我们这样有这么多工作吗
But I wonder if other offices have as much work as we do.

338
00:17:53,940 --> 00:17:57,860
我听说律师们希望能接各种案件
I heard lawyers want to see as many cases as they can.

339
00:17:58,610 --> 00:17:59,900
确实是这样
That's true.

340
00:18:00,070 --> 00:18:03,240
虽然千律师的行为看似鲁莽
Although it looks like Mr. Cheon acts recklessly,

341
00:18:03,320 --> 00:18:05,950
但稀奇的是 到目前为止 他没有一件案件是解决不了的
oddly, there wasn't a single case he couldn't resolve so far.

342
00:18:06,040 --> 00:18:08,700
那这次的事他也能解决吗
So, do you think he can resolve this case too?

343
00:18:09,290 --> 00:18:12,920
虽然他有点讨人厌 但如果是他的话 应该可以
Sometimes it's hard to stand him, but he probably will.

344
00:18:13,500 --> 00:18:15,750
天啊 他还真是讨人厌
Gosh. I really can't stand him.

345
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,420
但他撞车也太过分了
Still, he went too far by crashing into the car.

346
00:18:19,170 --> 00:18:22,260
所以我曾经问过他
I... once asked him

347
00:18:22,840 --> 00:18:25,510
为什么要做到这个地步
why he takes things so far.

348
00:18:27,220 --> 00:18:29,230
我们有权在安全的情况下工作
We have the right to work without dying.

349
00:18:29,310 --> 00:18:31,480
补充安全人员
Recruit more safety personnel!

350
00:18:31,560 --> 00:18:34,810
-补充人员 -补充人员
-Recruit more! -Recruit more!

351
00:18:34,900 --> 00:18:36,570
我们有权在安全的情况下工作
We have the right to work without dying!

352
00:18:36,650 --> 00:18:38,360
补充安全人员
Recruit more safety personnel!

353
00:18:38,440 --> 00:18:41,320
-补充人员 -补充人员
-Recruit more! -Recruit more!

354
00:18:41,400 --> 00:18:44,070
-补充人员 -补充人员
-Recruit more! -Recruit more!

355
00:19:00,800 --> 00:19:01,760
千律师
Mr. Cheon!

